special_days.type: ARRAY<STRUCT<date DATE, delivery ARRAY<STRUCT<`from` STRING, `to` STRING, reason STRING>>, pickup ARRAY<STRUCT<`from` STRING, `to` STRING, reason STRING>>>>
special_days.name: special_days
special_days.comment: Special days are overriding the schedule for the whole day, like '14.05.2018' (Monday) would override schedules.monday in JSON structure for 14th of May 2018. It is defining schedule for a specific day, instead of using a weekly one, e.g. for Christmas, New Years Eve, 1st of May. In practice combining schedules.* and special_days.* can be used for display purposes for customer who would be interested when vendor is open and when is not during the whole year. Schedule of vendor is resolved then in following order:special_days - overrides entire day from 'schedules' (e.g. different opening times during Christmas), schedules - basic weekly information about opening times. If no delivery or pickup are specified for a special day, vendor is considered as closed. In order to cover the whole day time range should be 00:00 - 24:00
